  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime of $25,000 and has demonstrated remorse and progress toward restitution. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, a 10-year sentence suggested by the spectator is disproportionately punitive given the non-violent nature of the offense and the defendant's lack of prior record. A 6-month incarceration period is appropriate to serve as a deterrent and punishment while allowing for the continued recovery of the embezzled funds.",
  "verdict": 6
}
